.TH VEX 1 "2026-03-15" "Vex" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
vex \- a structured data shell
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B vex
.RB [ \-l | \-\-login ]
.RB [ \-c
.IR command ]
.RB [ \-v | \-\-version ]
.RB [ \-h | \-\-help ]
.RI [ script
.RI [ args... ]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B Vex
is a modern shell that combines structured data pipelines with traditional
shell features.
It supports typed values (strings, integers, floats, booleans, lists,
records, closures), first-class functions, and built-in format parsers.
.PP
When invoked without arguments,
.B vex
starts an interactive session with line editing, syntax highlighting,
autosuggestion, and tab completion.
When given a
.I script
argument, it executes the file non-interactively.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-c " command"
Execute
.I command
as a string and exit.
.TP
.BR \-l ", " \-\-login
Start as a login shell, sourcing system and user login configuration files.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-version
Print the version number and exit.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print a brief usage summary and exit.
.TP
.IR script " [" args... ]
Run the given script file.
Arguments are accessible within the script as
.BR $0 ", " $1 ", ..., "
.BR $argv " (list of all arguments), and"
.BR $argc " (argument count)."
.SH SYNTAX
.SS Variables
.nf
\fBlet\fR x = 5          # immutable binding
\fBmut\fR y = 10         # mutable binding
echo $x              # variable expansion
.fi
.SS Strings
.nf
"hello $name"        # interpolated string
\(aqraw string\(aq         # literal string (no interpolation)
.fi
.SS Lists
.nf
[1, 2, 3]
.fi
.SS Records
.nf
{name: "vex", version: 1}
.fi
.SS Closures
.nf
{|x| $x * 2}
.fi
.SS Pipes
.nf
data | filter | transform      # structured data pipe
cmd |> cmd                     # byte stream pipe
.fi
.SS Ranges
.nf
1..10                # inclusive range
1..<10               # exclusive range
.fi
.SS Control Flow
.nf
\fBif\fR condition { ... } \fBelse\fR { ... }
\fBfor\fR x \fBin\fR $list { ... }
\fBwhile\fR condition { ... }
\fBloop\fR { ... }
\fBmatch\fR $val { pattern => action, ... }
\fBtry\fR { ... } \fBcatch\fR { |err| ... }
.fi
.SS Functions
.nf
\fBfn\fR name [params] { body }
.fi
.SS Operators
Arithmetic:
.BR + ", " \- ", " * ", " / ", " %
.br
Comparison:
.BR == ", " != ", " < ", " > ", " <= ", " >=
.br
Logical:
.BR and ", " or ", " not
.br
Regex match:
.B =~
.br
Error propagation:
.B ?
.SS External Commands
.nf
^command             # explicit external invocation
command              # resolved after builtins/functions
.fi
.SS Redirections
.nf
cmd > file           # stdout to file
cmd >> file          # stdout append
cmd 2> file          # stderr to file
cmd 2>> file         # stderr append
cmd < file           # stdin from file
cmd <<< "string"     # here-string
cmd 2>&1             # stderr to stdout
cmd <<EOF            # heredoc
\&...
EOF
.fi
.SS Background Execution
.nf
command &
.fi
.SS Conditional Chains
.nf
cmd1 && cmd2 || cmd3
.fi
.SH LINE EDITING
.B Vex
provides interactive line editing with two modes: Emacs (default) and Vi.
The editing mode is controlled by the
.B VEX_EDIT_MODE
environment variable.
.SS Emacs Mode (default)
.TP
.B Ctrl\-A / Ctrl\-E
Move to beginning / end of line.
.TP
.B Ctrl\-K
Kill text from cursor to end of line (saved to kill ring).
.TP
.B Ctrl\-U
Kill text from cursor to beginning of line.
.TP
.B Ctrl\-W
Kill word backward.
.TP
.B Ctrl\-Y
Yank (paste) from kill ring.
.TP
.B Ctrl\-R
Reverse incremental history search.
.TP
.B Ctrl\-L
Clear screen.
.TP
.B Ctrl\-X Ctrl\-E
Open current line in
.BR $EDITOR .
.TP
.B Ctrl\-Z
Suspend the shell (or foreground job).
.TP
.B Tab
Trigger completion (displayed as multi-column grid).
.TP
.B Shift\-Tab
Reverse cycle through completions.
.TP
.B Right arrow (at end of line)
Accept autosuggestion.
.TP
.B Ctrl\-Right
Accept one word from autosuggestion.
.SS Vi Mode
Activate by setting
.BR VEX_EDIT_MODE =vi.
.PP
.I Insert mode:
.TP
.BR i / a / A / I
Enter insert mode (before cursor / after cursor / end of line / beginning of line).
.PP
.I Normal mode movement:
.TP
.BR h / l
Move left / right.
.TP
.BR w / b / e
Word forward / backward / end.
.TP
.BR 0 " / " $
Beginning / end of line.
.PP
.I Delete:
.TP
.B x
Delete character under cursor.
.TP
.B dd
Clear entire line.
.TP
.BR dw " / " db " / " d$ " / " d0
Delete by motion.
.PP
.I Change:
.TP
.BR cc " / " cw " / " cb " / " c$ " / " c0 " / " C " / " S
Change by motion.
.PP
.I Other:
.TP
.B u
Undo.
.TP
.BR p " / " P
Paste after / before cursor.
.TP
.BR yy " / " yw " / " y$ " / " y0
Yank by motion.
.TP
.BR f / F / t / T " + " \fIchar\fR
Find / find backward / till / till backward the given character.
.TP
.B /
Search history (activates Ctrl\-R).
.SH BUILTINS
.B Vex
includes over 390 built-in commands covering file operations, data
manipulation, string processing, type conversion, math, and more.
.PP
Use the
.B help
command for documentation on a specific builtin:
.RS
.nf
help each
help str split
.fi
.RE
.PP
Use the
.B builtins
command to list all available builtins.
.SH PROMPT CUSTOMIZATION
The prompt can be configured using environment variables or callback closures.
.SS Format Specifiers
Set the
.B VEX_PROMPT
or
.B VEX_RPROMPT
environment variables using the following specifiers:
.TP
.B %d
Current working directory (full path).
.TP
.B %D
Basename of current working directory.
.TP
.B %g
Current Git branch name (empty if not in a repository).
.TP
.B %t
Current time in HH:MM format.
.TP
.B %T
Current time in HH:MM:SS format.
.TP
.B %n
Username.
.TP
.B %h
Hostname.
.TP
.B %e
Last exit code (displayed only if non-zero).
.TP
.B %v
Vi mode indicator:
.B INSERT
or
.BR NORMAL .
Empty when in Emacs mode.
.TP
.B %#
.B $
for normal users,
.B #
for root.
.TP
.BR %{ \fIstyle\fR }
ANSI style, e.g.\&
.BR %{bold,blue} " or " %{reset} .
.SS Prompt Closures
For full dynamic control, assign a closure:
.RS
.nf
prompt-fn {|| "my prompt> "}
rprompt-fn {|| $"(date now | format)"}
.fi
.RE
.SH HOOKS
Hooks allow running closures at specific shell lifecycle points.
.TP
.B preexec
Runs before each command is executed.
Receives the command string as an argument.
.RS
.nf
hook-add preexec {|cmd| log $cmd}
.fi
.RE
.TP
.B precmd
Runs before each prompt is displayed.
.RS
.nf
hook-add precmd {|| refresh-status}
.fi
.RE
.TP
.B chpwd
Runs when the working directory changes.
.RS
.nf
hook-add chpwd {|| ls}
.fi
.RE
.SH ABBREVIATIONS
Abbreviations expand inline as you type, before the command is executed.
.TP
.BI "abbr add " "name expansion"
Define an abbreviation.
.TP
.BI "abbr remove " name
Remove an abbreviation.
.TP
.B abbr list
List all defined abbreviations.
.PP
Example:
.RS
.nf
abbr add gs git status
abbr add gco git checkout
.fi
.RE
.SH COMPLETIONS
.TP
.BI "complete " "command" " \-w " "\(dqword1 word2 ...\(dq"
Register a static word list for completing arguments to
.IR command .
.TP
.BI "complete\-fn " "\(dqcommand\(dq" " " "closure"
Register a dynamic completion callback.
The closure receives the current prefix and must return a list of candidates.
.RS
.nf
complete-fn "myapp" {|prefix|
    myapp --completions $prefix | lines
}
.fi
.RE
.SH SHELL OPTIONS
Shell behaviour can be tuned with
.BR set :
.TP
.BR "set \-e" " / " "set \-o errexit"
Exit immediately if a command returns a non-zero status.
.TP
.BR "set \-x" " / " "set \-o xtrace"
Print each command before execution (prefixed with
.BR + ).
.TP
.BR "set \-u" " / " "set \-o nounset"
Treat references to undefined variables as errors.
.TP
.B set \-o noclobber
Prevent
.B >
from overwriting existing files (use
.B >|
to force).
.SH ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
.TP
.B VEX_PROMPT
Prompt format string (see
.BR "PROMPT CUSTOMIZATION" ).
.TP
.B VEX_RPROMPT
Right-side prompt format string.
.TP
.B VEX_EDIT_MODE
Line editing mode:
.B emacs
(default) or
.BR vi .
.TP
.B VEX_HISTSIZE
Maximum number of history entries to retain.
Default is 1000.
.TP
.BR VEX_COLOR_KEYWORD ", " VEX_COLOR_BUILTIN ", etc."
Syntax highlighting colours, specified as SGR parameter strings (e.g.\&
.BR "1;35" " for bold magenta)."
.TP
.B VEX_LOGIN_SHELL
Set to
.B 1
when running as a login shell.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/vex/config.vex
System-wide configuration, sourced on every invocation.
.TP
.I /etc/vex/profile.vex
System-wide login configuration, sourced only for login shells.
.TP
.I ~/.config/vex/config.vex
Per-user configuration, sourced on every invocation.
.TP
.I ~/.config/vex/profile.vex
Per-user login configuration, sourced only for login shells.
.TP
.I ~/.config/vex/history
Command history file.
.TP
.I ~/.config/vex/plugins.vex
List of enabled plugins for selective autoloading.
.TP
.I ~/.config/vex/themes/
User theme files.
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/vex/plugins/
Installed plugin packages.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.B Vex
returns the exit status of the last command executed, or zero if no
commands were run.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR bash (1),
.BR zsh (1),
.BR fish (1)
